titleStmt.title: The resolution and votes of the Parliament of England coneerning [sic] Major Generall Brown; for bringing him to a speedy tryall; and the particulars of the charge to be exhibited against him, touching the late insurrection and rebellion within the counties of Kent and Essex. : With the names of those alderman of the city of London, who are disabled from bearing any publique office or imployment in the commonwealth of England. : And a letter from the Major General to divers citizens touching the Parliament and army; a message to the lord major, and a proclamation to be proclaimed at the Royal Exchange; with severall proposals to the people of England.
